<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Charged S.C. Man Says He Was Drunk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KINGSTREE, S.C. (AP) -- One of two men accused of grabbing a man  
by the arm and dragging him alongside their pickup truck told 
police that he was drunk and couldn't remember much. 
</P>
<P>
	Eric W. Jones told police he and Arthur Marshall split a 12-pack  
of beer after work and all he remembers is the truck going into a 
ditch and then running through the woods, according to a police 
document reviewed Friday by The Associated Press. 
</P>
<P>
	Charone Green, 23, suffered leg and arm injuries but was not  
seriously hurt. He told police he was dragged for nearly a quarter 
mile. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones, 38, and Marshall, 34, were charged with assault and  
battery with intent to kill. Marshall also was charged with 
possession of a stolen vehicle -- the pickup. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, the two were ordered held in jail on $200,000 bond.  
</P>
<P>
	Williamsburg County Sheriff Kelvin Washington said he has found  
no evidence that the incident was racially motivated -- Jones and 
Marshall are white, and Green is black. The State Law Enforcement 
Division and the Federal Bureau of Investigation are looking into 
the case. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Green was grabbed and dragged when he  
approached a pickup truck that had slowed in front of his cousin's 
house on a rural road in the Bloomingvale community, about 90 miles 
east of Columbia. 
</P>
<P>
	A witness said Green broke free when the truck hit a culvert.  
</P>
<P>
	Washington backed off an earlier statement that drugs may have  
been involved. Green said there were no drugs involved, and he 
wasn't sure there was any racial motivation to the attack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
