<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Injuries Hit Stars and Avalanche </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- A series of injuries struck the Dallas Stars and  
the Colorado Avalanche in Game 4 of their Western Conference final 
series Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The Avalanche scratched left wing Valeri Kamensky, who sprained  
his right wrist in Game 3, and then lost right wing Milan Hejduk to 
a broken collar bone midway through the first period. 
</P>
<P>
	Hejduk, a strong rookie of the year candidate, was taken from  
McNichols Arena in an ambulance after being checked hard into the 
boards by Dallas defenseman Richard Matvichuk. A team spokesman 
said after the game that Hejduk would be out for the rest of the 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Hejduk has six goals and five assists in the playoffs.  
</P>
<P>
	Dallas forward Guy Carbonneau left the game late in the second  
period after his right leg got caught under the skate of Colorado's 
Dale Hunter. Carbonneau writhed on the ice before walking off on 
his own power and returned for the third period. 
</P>
<P>
	Kamensky sparked the Avalanche in the second round as they won  
four straight against Detroit after his return from a broken right 
forearm. 
</P>
<P>
	Injuries continued in the third period before Colorado won 3-2  
in overtime. Matvichuk was forced to leave the game with an 
apparent leg injury after a pileup at the boards with Colorado 
center Peter Forsberg, who was shaken up on the play. 
</P>
<P>
	Matvichuk returned for overtime.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
