<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> DaimlerChrysler Announces Recall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- DaimlerChrysler AG is recalling  
nearly 1 million minivans to check for short circuits that have 
caused air bags to inflate inadvertently. 
</P>
<P>
	The voluntary recall of 996,939 vehicles affects the Dodge  
Caravan, Plymouth Voyager and Chrysler Town &AMP; Country for the model 
years 1994-95, the automaker announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall announced Friday comes after about 35 reports of  
inadvertent deployment of driver's side air bags caused by a short 
in the wiring harness. Most of the incidents occurred when the 
vehicle was started. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no reported injuries.  
</P>
<P>
	Owners of the vehicles are expected to be notified in about a  
month. Any wiring shorts in the airbag systems will be repaired at 
no cost to owners, DaimlerChrysler said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
