<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Duval To Make Return at Memorial  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DUBLIN, Ohio (AP) -- David Duval, the world's top-ranked golfer,  
will return to the PGA Tour next week at the Memorial Tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Duval hasn't played since missing the cut three weeks ago at the  
Compaq Classic of New Orleans. Duval, who has four tournament wins 
this year, said he needed a mental break and took the last two tour 
events off. 
</P>
<P>
	The break will end Thursday in the opening round at Muirfield  
Village Golf Club. International Management Group of Cleveland, 
which represents Duval, confirmed Duval's participation Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The tournament will also feature Columbus native Jack Nicklaus,  
who designed the Muirfield course and has won the tournament twice 
in its 23-year history. 
</P>
<P>
	Fred Couples, who won the tournament last year, will try to  
become the first player to successfully defend the Memorial title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
