<HEADLINE> Smithsonian Museums Extend Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Beginning Saturday, four of Washington's most  
popular museums are extending their evening hours for part of the 
summer. 
</P>
<P>
	The International Gallery, the Museum of Natural History and the  
Museum of American History will stay open until 7:30 p.m. all week. 
The Air and Space Museum will close at 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	The normal closing hour of 5:30 p.m. will resume the day after  
Labor Day, Sept. 7. Admission to all four museums is free. 
</P>
