<HEADLINE> Tenn. Girl Dies in Struggle Over Gun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- A 10-year-old girl was shot to death  
on her birthday Friday and her 8-year-old cousin was critically 
wounded during a struggle over a a sawed-off shotgun they found in 
the woods. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the 11-year-old brother of one of the girls saw them  
playing with the gun and tried to take it away to protect them. 
They struggled and the weapon accidentally fired, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The older girl was shot in the chest. The younger girl, shot in  
the head, was in intensive care Friday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy was not hurt.  
</P>
<P>
	Police were investigating where the gun came from and said it  
might have been discarded earlier by a fleeing suspect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
