<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> B.B. King Wins Blues Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Blues guitarist B.B. King was named  
entertainer of the year at the 20th annual W.C. Handy Blues Awards. 
</P>
<P>
	He also won contemporary blues album of the year for ``Blues on  
the Bayou.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Other artists receiving awards Thursday night in more than one  
category were Etta James, best female soul artist and best soul 
album for ``Life, Love &AMP; the Blues''; Keb' Mo', contemporary male 
artist and best acoustic artist; and Susan Tedeschi, contemporary 
female artist and best new artist. 
</P>
<P>
	The winners were selected by The Blues Foundation, a nonprofit  
organization that promotes blues music. 
</P>
<P>
	The ceremony's hosts were Rufus Thomas and Joe Louis Walker, who  
performed with Elvis Presley's longtime guitarist, Scotty Moore. 
They played Presley's favorite, ``Mystery Train,'' and one of 
Walker's tunes, ``747''. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
