<DOCNO> APW19990528.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-28 18:41:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tampa's Saunders Put On 60-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Tony Saunders was placed on the 60-day disabled  
list by the Tampa Bay Devil Rays on Friday, two days after breaking 
his left arm while throwing a pitch. 
</P>
<P>
	Saunders suffered a spiral break of the left humerus, the bone  
from the shoulder to the elbow, in the third inning against Texas. 
He was released from a hospital in St. Petersburg on Thursday. His 
injury is expected to take at least 3-4 months to heal. 
</P>
<P>
	The Devil Rays called up right-hander Dave Eiland from Triple-A  
Durham to take Saunders' place on their roster. Eiland made nine 
starts for Durham, going 4-3 with a 3.67 ERA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
