<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> DaimlerChrysler Announces Recall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- Nearly 1 million Plymouth Voyager,  
Dodge Caravan and Chrysler Town &AMP; Country minivans are being 
recalled to check for short circuits that have caused air bags to 
inflate inadvertently. 
</P>
<P>
	DaimerChrysler AG announced the voluntary recall of 996,939  
vehicles on Friday. It covers the vehicles for model years 1994-95, 
the automaker said. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall comes after about 35 reports of inadvertent  
deployment of driver's side air bags caused by a short in the 
wiring harness. Most of the incidents happened when the vehicle was 
started. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no reported injuries.  
</P>
<P>
	DaimlerChrysler said vehicle owners will be notified in about a  
month and any wiring shorts in the airbag systems will be repaired 
at no cost to owners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
