<HEADLINE> Nashville Charity Director Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The director of the Nashville  
distribution warehouse for Feed The Children quit Friday amid an 
investigation into whether he and some of his employees stole 
donations to the charity. 
</P>
<P>
	Steve Highfill resigned a day after charity president and  
founder Larry Jones appointed a longtime friend to replace Highfill 
while Tennessee authorities and his own staff investigate. 
</P>
<P>
	The Tennessee Bureau of Investigation started a probe after  
WTVF-TV aired video of what the station said was Highfill and about 
six other administrative employees taking home boxes of donated 
goods. 
</P>
<P>
