agents carrying out boxes and bags of brand-name clothing, shoes, 
videos, blankets, food and other goods they suspect were donated 
for poor people. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this week, Highfill told WTVF he saw nothing wrong with  
allowing administrative staff to take donated items. No one 
answered the telephone Friday at his home. 
