<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marlins' Boles Misses Another Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Florida Marlins manager John Boles missed Friday's  
game against the Cincinnati Reds because of a cervical sprain and 
spasms in his neck. 
</P>
<P>
	Boles missed two games this month after undergoing back surgery.  
It has not been determined if the back surgery is related to Boles' 
latest malady. He has already started physical therapy. 
</P>
<P>
	Third base coach Fredi Gonzalez took over the club for the third  
time this season and bench coach Joe Breeden moved to third. 
Gonzalez is still seeking his first win as interim manager. 
</P>
<P>
	``I got another chance at getting my first `W','' Gonzalez said.  
``Bolesy only missed two games after back surgery, so a neck spasm 
will probably keep him out for about 40 minutes.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The results of an MRI on Boles' stiff neck Friday were negative.  
He's listed day-to-day, but will most likely return Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
