	EU Raids Danish Sugar Manufacturer  
</P>
<P>
	BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) -- European Union antitrust investigators  
have raided the offices of Danish sugar manufacturer Danisco as 
part of a probe into possible pricing abuses, the EU said today. 
The EU's probe is focussing on the Danish and Swedish markets, said 
Stefan Rating, spokesman for Karel Van Miert, the EU's competition 
commissioner. The European Commission is cooperating with Danish 
authorities on the case, Rating told reporters. He did not say when 
the commission will announce its findings from the raids and 
declined to provide further details. 

</P>
