informant whose information helped lead to the arrest of a former 
employee. The executives, who were not identified, were suspended 
with pay pending the outcome of an investigation, the firm 
announced yesterday. Morgan Stanley, the nation's largest 
securities firm, said it had made a ``mistake in judgment'' last 
year when it paid a middleman, Charles Joseph Luethke, to help set 
up a police sting operation against Christian Curry. Curry had been 
fired and was contemplating filing a discrimination claim against 
the firm when the sting was arranged. 

