<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 20 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened modestly higher in  
early trading. The Dow Jones industrial average is ahead 20 points 
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock 
Exchange hold a 3-2 lead over losers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 13 points and the Standard &AMP;  
Poor's 500 Index is up five points. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts are looking for light pre-holiday trading today.  
Technical analysts say the market doesn't appear close to 
experiencing a wash-out, because volume has been relatively thin 
this week, as the market has experienced volatility. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, the Dow industrials average suffered its worst  
decline of the year so far, in what traders describe as a market 
fueled by inflation fear. 
</P>
<P>
	On the economic slate, the Commerce Department reports that  
personal income rose 0.5 percent in April, while spending 0.4 
percent. 
</P>
<P>
	That indicates while the economic remains vibrant, at least one  
measure of savings remains quite low. 
</P>
<P>
	The bond market is steady. The price of the 30-year Treasury was  
unchanged, while the benchmark yield stood at 5.84 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of Dow component General Motors are in the spotlight, as  
the automaker completes the spinoff of its Delphi Automotive 
Systems unit. 

</P>
</TEXT>
