<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man in Wash. Standoff Found Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SHORELINE, Wash. (AP) -- A man fleeing a hit-and-run freeway  
accident ran to a house and attacked two women Friday, killing one 
and breaking the other's neck, authorities said. He barricaded 
himself in a second house and died in a shootout with police. 
</P>
<P>
	The man was found dead at about 8:45 p.m., eight hours after the  
standoff began, King County Sheriff Dave Reichert said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police in the nearby town of Brier said the slayings of a woman  
and a young boy earlier in the day were connected to the gunman, 
who was not identified. Police did not elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	Police were called to the area by a neighbor who heard a woman  
scream. When officers arrived, a man holed up in a nearby house 
began firing. 
</P>
<P>
	Two women, both in their 60s, were assaulted in the yard outside  
a home, possibly with a garden tool, police said. One was 
bludgeoned to death, and the other was in critical condition with a 
broken neck. 
</P>
<P>
	SWAT teams converged on the scene and helped evacuate nearby  
homes. Students in a nearby elementary school were ordered to stay 
inside. 
</P>
<P>
	The house where the man was holed up contained a large number of  
weapons and he fired dozens of shots before he died, officers said. 
Reichert said his officers responded with just one sniper's shot. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a sad thing and it's a tough decision to make,'' Reichert  
said. ``But in this case it was the right thing to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A female deputy was in serious condition with a fractured skull  
and cuts on her face apparently suffered when a bullet struck her 
vehicle, said Larry Zalin, a spokesman for Harborview Medical 
Center in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses told police they saw the suspect jump out of his car  
and run into the neighborhood after his car struck Anthony Venegas' 
motorcycle on Interstate 5 and caught fire. Venegas, 64, lost his 
left leg in the crash. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident and standoff forced police to close I-5 in both  
directions at the start of the evening rush hour for the holiday 
weekend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
