<HEADLINE> Lindros Given Clean Bill of Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Philadelphia Flyers center Eric Lindros has  
recovered from the collapsed lung he suffered last month and has 
been officially cleared to play hockey again. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's looking great and doing great, and he's back to his  
playing weight'' of 236 pounds, Dr. Larry Kaiser, chief of thoracic 
surgery at the Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania, said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindros suffered the collapsed right lung April 1 in a game  
against Nashville, and did not play the rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Besides meeting with doctors, Lindros and his agent and father,  
Carl, were in Philadelphia for a two-hour meeting with Flyers 
chairman Ed Snider. Officials from either side declined to comment 
on the franchise center's contract status. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindros has a handshake agreement for a one-year, $8.5 million  
contract extension with Philadelphia, but can be a restricted free 
agent July 1. The Flyers would have the right to match any offer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
