<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Guilty Plea in Wyo. Murder Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LARAMIE, Wyo. (AP) -- A man pleaded innocent Friday to charges  
that he killed the mother of Russell Henderson, who is serving two 
life sentences for the murder of gay college student Matthew 
Shepard. 
</P>
<P>
	Dennis Leroy Menefee Jr., 28, of Hastings, Fla., is accused of  
picking up Cindy Lee Dixon on a street corner, sexually assaulting 
her and then kicking her out of his vehicle on a bitter winter 
night. He remains jailed on a first-degree murder charge. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Dixon, 40, died of hypothermia. Her body was discovered Jan.  
3 on a snow-covered rural road north of Laramie. 
</P>
<P>
	Menefee had been living in Laramie when she died, authorities  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Dixon's son, Russell Henderson, 21, pleaded guilty to murder  
and kidnapping in the October beating death of Shepard. 
</P>
<P>
	The second suspect in Shepard's death, Aaron McKinney, 21, goes  
on trial Oct. 11. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Shepard's and Ms. Dixon's deaths were not  
related. 
</P>
</TEXT>
